name: My First Sorting Problem
statement: You are given two integers $$$x$$$ and $$$y$$$. Output two integers: the minimum of $$$x$$$ and $$$y$$$, followed by the maximum of $$$x$$$ and $$$y$$$.
inputFormat: The first line contains a single integer $$$t$$$ ($$$1 \leq t \leq 100$$$) â€” the number of test cases. The only line of each test case contains two space-separated integers $$$x$$$ and $$$y$$$ ($$$0 \leq x, y \leq 9$$$).
outputFormat: For each test case, output two integers: the minimum of $$$x$$$ and $$$y$$$, followed by the maximum of $$$x$$$ and $$$y$$$.
